cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

This paper discusses the software architecture for indexing and searching wiki pages, which involves natural language processing and database design. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also mentions the use of a visual tool for database design, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper includes experiments and comparisons of different index databases, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
